The paper focuses on natural language processing tasks such as question answering and question generation, which are typically studied in the subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also uses machine learning techniques such as sequence-to-sequence learning and recurrent neural networks, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves probabilistic modeling and correlation analysis, which are relevant to neural networks and statistical learning (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on three datasets, which suggests a focus on information retrieval (cs.IR).
